&quot;That will be fine.  We&#39;ve been so busy here thay I haven&#39;t had a chance to
do much of anything,&quot; said Perseus, returning the salute.

Just then Depthcharge came out of the command center door, followed by
Kenzo.

&quot;Ah, so you were the maximal in the CR chamber.  I am Perseus, the leader of
the Pasificus Maximals.&quot;

&quot;Depthcharge, Maximal Security,&quot; he replied with a formal tone.  &quot;If you
need to interrogate someone, I have some experience with that and may be
able to help.&quot;  He turned to Tuscon, &quot;May I accompany you?&quot;

On Mar 30, 2010 10:20 AM, &quot;Sandy&quot; &lt;magicquartz@...&gt; wrote:

Tucson had gotten Lord Elder&#39;s message.  He wasn&#39;t quite sure who
Nightstrike worked for, and was happy for the word up.

&quot;Thank you Lord Elder, I should have asked that before I left, my bad.
Tucson Prime out.  Sorry Lord Perseus, it was Lord Elder. I&#39;m glad he
contacted me because I didn&#39;t know that Nightstrike wasn&#39;t one of Hydras&#39;
men.  But, I still need to question him of course.  It&#39;s great to actually
see you this time, sir.&quot;

He salutes Lord Perseus, and then looks over to Talon who smiles back to
him.  He had not forgotten her.  He had strong feelings for her and was
happy to see her for the first time.

&quot; You&#39;re even more beautiful than I imagined before I could see you.  When
I&#39;m finished, I&#39;d really like to - well.. You know um, get to know you a
little better..  Er... I&#39;m not good at this..  Anyway, I have to go.&quot;

He visibly turns a slight shade of red around his optics.  He then gathers
himself to prepare to question Nightstrike as to Unicron&#39;s intentions.  He
knew he had several things happening at once, and to be a Prime to him,
meant he had to be well rounded.  He also felt that Unicron&#39;s objectives had
something to do with the opression that was hovering over the planet.  As
always, he was curious as to why things were happening.

&quot; If it&#39;s all right with both of you, I&#39;d like to ask Nightstrike some
questions.  When in doubt, seek the answers from unlikely resources...
 Something I kind of learned on my own.&quot;


